  "What is the spherical excess of a triangle?": "",
  "Triangles on a Sphere The sum of angles in a spherical triangle is greater than 180° and less than 540°. Spherical — triangle angle sum > 180°. The other options — 'The difference between 360° and the angle sum', 'The perimeter of the triangle divided by π', and '180° minus the largest angle' — are related concepts but do not correctly answer this specific question.": "",
  "What is a geodesic on a sphere?": "",
  "A geodesic is the shortest path between two points on a curved surface. On a sphere, geodesics are great circle arcs (like the equator). The answer is The shortest path between two points, which is a great circle arc. The other options — 'Any path on the surface of the sphere', 'A line of latitude', and 'A spiral path connecting the poles' — are related concepts but do not correctly answer this specific question.": "",
